<span id="freeTextContainer12868870138710379104">This book is a family saga on the Godwin&apos;s family told over a period of fifty years in their Welsh estate, Oxmoon. I must agree with Misfit, this book is without any doubt the best book written by Susan Howatch, even if I did loved Cashelmara and Penmarric. The parallel with the real historical characters is fabulous. As in any book by SH, is hard to tell which is my favorite character but I&apos;m still divided between Kester and Hal.</span>
